texts.textentryhtml: Junius S. Morgan [1867-1932, Lugt 1536]; bequeathed to Princeton University Art Museum, 1932.

This portrait represents a gentleman of upper- and middle-class Netherlandish society. The medal on which Johannes Kellenberch’s portrait is based bears a coat of arms on the back, indicating his aristocratic lineage.
